defaultLawrencedefault Tomlinsondefault: I don’t have any micro solutions in the report but, as Sir Andrew Large also suggests, the structural flaws within GRG should immediately be fixed, so one would wonder why West Register was buying properties and operating properties of its customers. People have come to me and said, “Exactly what you have described happened to me but I didn’t know that West Register was RBS. I didn’t know two years ago that RBS bought my business or my properties”. They didn’t know.
default&#xa0;
defaultQ59 default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
