defaultQ95 default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultMr Newmark:default Forget the individual. I think many MPs will have coming into their surgeries particularly people who have small businesses where this sort of base takes place. Just to give an example, if you receive a commission of, let’s say, £40,000 for a particular deal and you can pull the rug from under that business three months later and make £400,000, that tends to happen. I don’t want to tar all institutions with that brush, but certainly it seemed to be going on, again from anecdotal evidence from my meetings with GRG in particular and also Bibby. There seemed to be almost an incentive to salesmen to pull the rug from under these businesses. I would be interested in your comment on that. 
defaultLawrencedefault Tomlinsondefault: I came across it and it was anecdotal evidence that I had. I did ask for examples of it but I don’t believe that they were forthcoming to any kind of degree. 
defaultMr Newmark:default But you accept the principle that it has been going on? 
defaultLawrencedefault Tomlinsondefault: Yes. The thing is you put somebody into a contract for five years, you sell them this thing, and then you create a default and you end up charging the commission for the next three years even though they have only been in it for six months.
