defaultCan I come quickly to my second question, which is that in your report at the end you have under “Solutions” your three main points, A, B and C. C was the competition issue, which the Chairman asked you about at the beginning so I don’t want to go there again. I want to ask you about the other two. A was business protection and B was conflicts of interest. Business protection is effectively the equivalent of a chapter 11? 
defaultLawrencedefault Tomlinsondefault: Yes, but not as clumsy. I have spoken to the insolvency people in Business, Innovation &amp; Skills and chapter 11 does not seem to be on the agenda. But payable on demand loans, immediate repayment, I think there should be maybe a cooling-off period, 30 days before a bank can call it in, or 60 days, to give the business an opportunity to move. If the bank is going to sell the debt, there should be first option to the business and not have it sold to someone who is buying the business.
