default&#xa0;
defaultQ105 default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultJohn Thurso:default The second one is conflict of interest. You made the very good point that the Enterprise Act 2002 meant HMRC is no longer the first creditor and that therefore whoever is an asset holder becomes a prime creditor and there is an incentive for the person holding that security to put the bank under, whereas in the old days, when HMRC was the first creditor, there was an incentive to keep the thing going because the money would go to HMRC. You further note that there are all sorts of things in conflict, like the bank wants a business review, it is the same companies and they do a lot of work for them. 
defaultLawrencedefault Tomlinsondefault: They do the admin. 
